== Events == * In the 2nd year of the Kannin era ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1018]] – November 26): Fujiwara no Michinaga’s daughter, Yaneko, became Empress Dowager, and her sister, Takeko, was installed as the consort (chūgū) of Emperor Go-Ichijō. During this time, Michinaga himself composed a poem celebrating his own prosperity: “I regard this world as my world, and I see no defect in the waning moon.” * In the 2nd year of the Kōan era ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1279]] – November 21): Abutsu-ni set out on a journey, as recorded in her "Diary of the Sixteenth Night." * In the 1st year of the Genkō era ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1321]] – November 6): Emperor Go-Daigo initiated his new government policy known as "Kenmu no Shinsei."
== Births == * In the 2nd year of the Bunsei era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1819]] – December 3): Abe Masahiro, a senior councilor (Rōjū) of the Bakumatsu period and lord of the Fukuyama Domain, was born (died 1857). * In the 11th year of the Tenpō era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1840]] – November 9): Kuroda Kiyotaka, who later served as the 2nd Prime Minister of Japan, was born (died 1900).
== Deaths == * In the 8th year of the Tenchi era ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[669]] – November 14): Emperor Tenji’s trusted retainer, known as Nakatomi no Kamatari (also referred to as Fujiwara no Kamatari), a founding ancestor of the Fujiwara clan, died (born 614). * In the 13th year of the Genroku era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1700]] – November 26): Tokugawa Mitsutomo, the 2nd lord of the Owari Domain, died (born 1625). * In the 1st year of the Kyōwa era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1801]] – November 21): Matsudaira Yoshitō, the lord of the Takasu Domain, died (born 1738).
