{{Not to be confused with|October 16|qq=October 16}}[[Category:Days of the Japanese Lunisolar Calendar]]<!--why is this category always showing up as 347 members?--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=十月十六|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 10월 16일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar October|qq=}} '''October 16''' is the 16th day of the month {{ill|October (Lunisolar)|ja|10月 (旧暦)|lt=October (Kannazuki)|1=Kannazuki|2=ja|3=10月 (旧暦)|1=Kannazuki|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/October (Lunisolar)|13=User:Immanuelle/Kannazuki|qq=}}, the 10th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its Rokuyō is {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}}, and the day is {{ill|Senshō|ja|先勝|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senshō|qq=}}.
== Events == * In the 2nd year of the Kannin era ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1018]] – November 26): Fujiwara no Michinaga’s daughter, Yaneko, became Empress Dowager, and her sister, Takeko, was installed as the consort (chūgū) of Emperor Go-Ichijō. During this time, Michinaga himself composed a poem celebrating his own prosperity: “I regard this world as my world, and I see no defect in the waning moon.” * In the 2nd year of the Kōan era ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1279]] – November 21): Abutsu-ni set out on a journey, as recorded in her "Diary of the Sixteenth Night." * In the 1st year of the Genkō era ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1321]] – November 6): Emperor Go-Daigo initiated his new government policy known as "Kenmu no Shinsei."
== Births == * In the 2nd year of the Bunsei era ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1819]] – December 3): Abe Masahiro, a senior councilor (Rōjū) of the Bakumatsu period and lord of the Fukuyama Domain, was born (died 1857). * In the 11th year of the Tenpō era ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1840]] – November 9): Kuroda Kiyotaka, who later served as the 2nd Prime Minister of Japan, was born (died 1900).
== Deaths == * In the 8th year of the Tenchi era ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[669]] – November 14): Emperor Tenji’s trusted retainer, known as Nakatomi no Kamatari (also referred to as Fujiwara no Kamatari), a founding ancestor of the Fujiwara clan, died (born 614). * In the 13th year of the Genroku era ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1700]] – November 26): Tokugawa Mitsutomo, the 2nd lord of the Owari Domain, died (born 1625). * In the 1st year of the Kyōwa era ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1801]] – November 21): Matsudaira Yoshitō, the lord of the Takasu Domain, died (born 1738).
